<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-09-0587 </DOCNO><TEXT>Expert Systems or Database, none of those systems meet completely theuser needs, each of them having attractive features. The authors proposeto unify these two approaches in order to make profit of the best functionalitiesof each one. The integrating tool is based on logic programming (Prolog).The architecture of the system includes: a general Expert System dealingwith knowledge (schemata of the databases, coherency, deduction) andmeta-knowledge (rules, theories, control); a communication processormanaging the interface with the DBMS (the DBMSs are considered as processorsof big amount of data); sophisticated user interfaces depending on theuser status and activities.</TEXT></DOC>